               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1276" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1276" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1276" type="surname" value="RIDDELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1276" type="given" value="BARTHOLOMEW WILLIAM"></interp>BARTHOLOMEW WILLIAM RIDDELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am steward of the barque the <hi rend="italic">Dale Park</hi>, which was in the West India Dock—I saw-the sky-light safe about twenty minutes past five, on the 20th of Oct.—the watchman came to me about ten minutes to six—the sky-light was then off, and the sextant was gone—it belonged to the captain, Samuel Snell—it has not been found since—the sideboard drawer was open, and other things were gone.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1277" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1277" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1277" type="surname" value="GLADWELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1277" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS GLADWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an officer. At a quarter-past six that day the prisoner came to the dock-gate, and presented me with a pass for a sex<lb></lb>tant—I heard something rattle in it, and I said, "What is this?"—he said, "Some of the glasses are broken, I am going to get it repaired; I am learning navigation"—I believed, from the pass, that be belonged to a vessel—he was coming out of Limehouse basin entrance—there were a great many people came out, but none with a sextant.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> The person who opens the door at the Haymarket, can prove I was at the theatre door that evening before the gates were open; I went in, and after the first act I came out, and went to a public-house; the man said, "Can I have half a pint of beer with you;" I said, "Yes."</p>
